 Uses of Supernatural Power: The Transformation of Popular Religion in Medieval and Early-Modern Europe |last=Klaniczay |first=G\u00e1bor |others=Susan Singerman (translator) |year=1990 |publisher=Princeton University Press |location=Princeton |isbn=978-0691073774 |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=The Witch Hunt in Early Modern Europe |edition=second |last=Levack |first=Brian P. |year=1995 |publisher=Longman |location=London and New York |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |last=Medway |first=Gareth J. |title=Lure of the Sinister: The Unnatural History of Satanism |publisher=New York University Press |location=New York and London |year=2001 |isbn=9780814756454 |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=Witch Hunting in Southwestern Germany 1562\u20131684: The Social and Intellectual Foundations |last=Midelfort |first=H.C.E. |year=1972 |location=Stanford |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=The Witch-Cult in Western Europe |last=Murray |first=Margaret A. |year=1962 |origyear=1921 |publisher=Clarendon Press |location=Oxford |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=The God of the Witches |last=Murray |first=Margaret A. |year=1952 |origyear=1931 |publisher=Faber and Faber |location=London |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title= Between the Living and the Dead: A Perspective on Witches and Seers in the Early Modern Age |last=P\u00f3cs |first=\u00c9va |authorlink=\u00c9va P\u00f3cs |year=1999 |publisher=Central European Academic Press |location=Budapest |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=The Witch in History: Early Modern and Twentieth-Century Representations |last=Purkiss |first=Diane |authorlink=Diane Purkiss |year=1996 |publisher=Routledge |location=Abingdon |isbn=978-0415087629 |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=Witch Craze |last=Roper |first=Lyndal |location=New Haven |publisher=Yale University Press |year=2004 |ref=harv}}\n:{{cite book |title=A Razor for a Goat: A Discussion of Certain Problems in Witchcraft and Diabolism |last=Rose |first=Elliot |year=1962 |publisher= Toronto University Press |locat